    <stitle>RECONDITIONING ROTORS - DESCRIPTION - INSPECTION</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="0">
        <title>INSPECTION</title>
        <para>A scheduled inspection program for the brake system will greatly reduce brake- per-mile cost compared to
            reacting to brake problems when they occur. Although there is no specific timetable recommended, regular and
            thorough inspections are important.
        </para>
        <para>When following the inspection procedures outlined, you do not need to remove the rotor. The common rotor
            problems shown in this section can be identified by removing the tire and rim, and inspecting the rotor.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
